{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/host-sfb-meetings-like-a-pro/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"cf2c3b90-7e64-5f22-9a3f-5d56e37b86e1","parent":{"relativePath":"blog/2019-01-29-host-sfb-meetings-like-a-pro.md"},"fields":{"slug":"/host-sfb-meetings-like-a-pro/"},"html":"<p>Please note that <strong>I only focus on technical aspects</strong> (configuration of Outlook and Skype for Business) and assume that you know the basics (like preparing the agenda, clarifying the purpose of the meeting, choosing appropriate content for the audience) I also assume that your Skype for Business is working correctly (you have enough bandwidth, stable connection).</p>\n<h2 id=\"checklist-only\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#checklist-only\" aria-label=\"checklist only permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Checklist only</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Make sure to specify if you want to receive responses to the invitation</li>\n<li>Limit the presenter role to the people who need it</li>\n<li>Mute all attendees and block attendees' video</li>\n<li>Upload the presentation before the meeting</li>\n<li>Make the presentation downloadable (including notes and annotations) if you wish</li>\n<li>While sharing content other than presentation â€“ use desktop sharing</li>\n</ul>\n<!--more-->\n<h2 id=\"table-of-contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#table-of-contents\" aria-label=\"table of contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Table of Contents</h2>\n<div class=\"table-of-contents\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#frequent-issues\">Frequent issues</a></li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#start-with-the-invitation\">Start with the invitation</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#response-options\">Response options</a></li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#skype-meeting-options\">Skype meeting options</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#presenter-or-attendee\">Presenter or attendee?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#available-skype-meeting-options\">Available Skype meeting options</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#during-the-meeting\">During the meeting</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#powerpoint-presentation\">PowerPoint presentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#participant-actions\">Participant actions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#desktop-sharing\">Desktop sharing</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"frequent-issues\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#frequent-issues\" aria-label=\"frequent issues permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Frequent issues</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>People join with unmuted microphone and they interrupt the audio before they even realize everyone can hear them</li>\n<li>Presenter is removed from the meeting by misclick of one of the participants</li>\n<li>Someone ends the meeting in the middle of the conversation</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Below I'm addressing these issues and also suggest what you can do more.</p>\n<h2 id=\"start-with-the-invitation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#start-with-the-invitation\" aria-label=\"start with the invitation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Start with the invitation</h2>\n<p>When you create the meeting, there are some useful options which could make your life easier (and in the same time, make you look more professional):</p>\n<h3 id=\"response-options\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#response-options\" aria-label=\"response options permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Response options</h3>\n<p>On 'Meeting' ribbon in your Outlook you can specify whether you want to receive all the responses to your mailbox. For big meetings it's usually good to unmark the option and avoid reply flood (if you really need it, you can <a href=\"https://support.office.com/en-us/article/use-inbox-rules-in-outlook-com-4b094371-a5d7-49bd-8b1b-4e4896a7cc5d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">create a rule in Outlook</a> to redirect the replies to a folder).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1005px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d6088ab58e9e4c88139bbc9676af5958/18c13/2019-01-31%2015_35_58-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.505307855626324%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-31 15_35_58-Untitled - Meeting.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-31 15_35_58-Untitled - Meeting.png\"\n        src=\"/static/d6088ab58e9e4c88139bbc9676af5958/18c13/2019-01-31%2015_35_58-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d6088ab58e9e4c88139bbc9676af5958/1f09d/2019-01-31%2015_35_58-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png 471w,\n/static/d6088ab58e9e4c88139bbc9676af5958/f1901/2019-01-31%2015_35_58-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png 942w,\n/static/d6088ab58e9e4c88139bbc9676af5958/18c13/2019-01-31%2015_35_58-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png 1005w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1005px) 100vw, 1005px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The invitees will see the information that the organizer hasn't requested the response for the invitation.</p>\n<p>When someone accepts the meeting you, as an organizer, won't receive the responses but also <strong>won't be able to track who accepted the meeting</strong>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"skype-meeting-options\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#skype-meeting-options\" aria-label=\"skype meeting options permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Skype meeting options</h3>\n<p><em>It is important to set the settings during the initial planning. Any changes performed later might not reflect immediately!</em></p>\n<p>To change the meeting options, you need to go to 'Meeting Options' on the ribbon:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 415px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e95f4bbaa4bb48f59bac67f0728b6e59/73926/2019-01-31%2015_36_16-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 46.74698795180723%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-31 15_36_16-Untitled - Meeting.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-31 15_36_16-Untitled - Meeting.png\"\n        src=\"/static/e95f4bbaa4bb48f59bac67f0728b6e59/73926/2019-01-31%2015_36_16-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e95f4bbaa4bb48f59bac67f0728b6e59/73926/2019-01-31%2015_36_16-Untitled%20-%20Meeting.png 415w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 415px) 100vw, 415px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here's the list of options available for Skype for Business meeting with the suggested configuration:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 941px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2886dd2a5cfbfbe15b0a76f412322e15/a8417/2019-01-29%2009_37_13-Test%20meeting%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.955414012738856%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-29 09_37_13-Test meeting - Meeting.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-29 09_37_13-Test meeting - Meeting.png\"\n        src=\"/static/2886dd2a5cfbfbe15b0a76f412322e15/a8417/2019-01-29%2009_37_13-Test%20meeting%20-%20Meeting.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2886dd2a5cfbfbe15b0a76f412322e15/1f09d/2019-01-29%2009_37_13-Test%20meeting%20-%20Meeting.png 471w,\n/static/2886dd2a5cfbfbe15b0a76f412322e15/a8417/2019-01-29%2009_37_13-Test%20meeting%20-%20Meeting.png 941w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 941px) 100vw, 941px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"presenter-or-attendee\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#presenter-or-attendee\" aria-label=\"presenter or attendee permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Presenter or attendee?</h4>\n<p>Before going further it's important to understand the difference beetween the presenter and an attendee.</p>\n<p><strong>Presenter</strong>, in contrary to <strong>attendee</strong> is able to do anything with the meeting (share audio and video, present desktop, mute and remove participants and even <strong>end the meeting</strong>).</p>\n<p>An <strong>attendee</strong> can only hear, chat and talk, nothing else.</p>\n<p><strong>During the meeting, any presenter is able to make another attendee a presenter</strong> by right-clicking the attendee and choosing <code class=\"language-text\">Make a presenter</code> option:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 444px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/357ff2909c548580ee31548e8dc71b92/9b7bd/2019-01-29%2009_47_22-Meeting.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-29 09_47_22-Meeting.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-29 09_47_22-Meeting.png\"\n        src=\"/static/357ff2909c548580ee31548e8dc71b92/9b7bd/2019-01-29%2009_47_22-Meeting.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/357ff2909c548580ee31548e8dc71b92/9b7bd/2019-01-29%2009_47_22-Meeting.png 444w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 444px) 100vw, 444px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"available-skype-meeting-options\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#available-skype-meeting-options\" aria-label=\"available skype meeting options permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Available Skype meeting options</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>These people don't have to wait in the lobby<br>\nYou can select who will have to wait until <strong>presenter</strong> allows them to enter the meeting. I recommend setting this to <code class=\"language-text\">Anyone (no restrictions)</code> to not have to approve each user entering the meeting.  </p>\n<p>Two options below are self-explanatory. <code class=\"language-text\">Callers get in directly</code> allows people who call in with a phone to be connected automatically. The second one <code class=\"language-text\">Announce when people enter or leave</code> is usually not recommended for large meetings (imagine 200 people entering and each of them being announced)</p>\n</li>\n<li>Who's a presenter?<br>\nIt's crucial to choose the appropriate option here. I recommend <code class=\"language-text\">Only me, the meeting organizer</code> (provided that you are sure you join the meeting).\nThe alternate option would be to choose the presenters upfront (the option <code class=\"language-text\">People I choose</code> lets you to add anyone you want to the list of presenters)  </li>\n<li>\n<p>Do you want to limit participation?<br>\nI recommend choosing <code class=\"language-text\">Mute all attendees</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">Block attendees&#39; video</code>. Therefore, all the participants who join the meeting will be muted by default. They won't be able to speak until the audience is unmuted (see <a href=\"#participant-actions\">participant actions</a> to learn how to do this). </p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: people who joined via phone will still be able to unmute themselves.</p>\n<p>IM (chat) is usually useful to confirm that people are able to hear you and can see the presentation.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can also check which setting is recommended for your scenario <a href=\"https://support.office.com/en-us/article/change-participant-settings-for-skype-for-business-meetings-9175e297-de5f-43b2-8e0f-85cc05e24986\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">on Microsoft KB article</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"during-the-meeting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#during-the-meeting\" aria-label=\"during the meeting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>During the meeting</h2>\n<h3 id=\"powerpoint-presentation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#powerpoint-presentation\" aria-label=\"powerpoint presentation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>PowerPoint presentation</h3>\n<p>If you plan to share PowerPoint presentation, make sure to use <code class=\"language-text\">Share PowerPoint Files</code> option instead of desktop sharing. This will upload the presentation to Skype for Business server and it won't rely on your network connectivity. <strong>Remember that it takes some time to upload the file especially if it contains many slides</strong>.</p>\n<p>If you want people to be able to download the presentation you can allow everyone to download it. By default it's limited to the presenters (see <a href=\"#presenter-or-attendee\">Presenter or attendee?</a> and once again make sure you've chosen the proper option).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 705px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7f1ed6d05e5f021529a812c562e339cb/d2cbc/2019-01-29%2010_24_55-.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.73673036093418%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-29 10_24_55-.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-29 10_24_55-.png\"\n        src=\"/static/7f1ed6d05e5f021529a812c562e339cb/d2cbc/2019-01-29%2010_24_55-.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7f1ed6d05e5f021529a812c562e339cb/1f09d/2019-01-29%2010_24_55-.png 471w,\n/static/7f1ed6d05e5f021529a812c562e339cb/d2cbc/2019-01-29%2010_24_55-.png 705w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 705px) 100vw, 705px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: Be aware that people who can download the presentation, as well as all the presenters, will see the notes which you made to the slides!</p>\n<h3 id=\"participant-actions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#participant-actions\" aria-label=\"participant actions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Participant actions</h3>\n<p>Below the list of participants you can find 'Participant Actions' button:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 697px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0efdb0e3761cdde8a6984ecf1ff5d7a4/7422e/2019-01-29%2010_44_12-.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.016985138004245%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-29 10_44_12-.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-29 10_44_12-.png\"\n        src=\"/static/0efdb0e3761cdde8a6984ecf1ff5d7a4/7422e/2019-01-29%2010_44_12-.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0efdb0e3761cdde8a6984ecf1ff5d7a4/1f09d/2019-01-29%2010_44_12-.png 471w,\n/static/0efdb0e3761cdde8a6984ecf1ff5d7a4/7422e/2019-01-29%2010_44_12-.png 697w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 697px) 100vw, 697px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Once you click it, new window will be opened with various options available:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 701px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/01c2c52f8ee5e8f9ffd5b71949e3714e/49217/2019-01-29%2010_57_02-.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.2484076433121%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2019-01-29 10_57_02-.png\"\n        title=\"2019-01-29 10_57_02-.png\"\n        src=\"/static/01c2c52f8ee5e8f9ffd5b71949e3714e/49217/2019-01-29%2010_57_02-.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/01c2c52f8ee5e8f9ffd5b71949e3714e/1f09d/2019-01-29%2010_57_02-.png 471w,\n/static/01c2c52f8ee5e8f9ffd5b71949e3714e/49217/2019-01-29%2010_57_02-.png 701w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mute audience<br>\nUsing that option will mute everyone except you. Presenters will be able to unmute, but attendees wonâ€™t be until you go to the same place and click â€˜Unmute audienceâ€™. Quite useful option.  </li>\n</ul>\n<p>  <strong>Note</strong>: people who joined via phone will still be able to unmute themselves.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No meeting IM<br>\nCan be useful in some cases to avoid interruption from users during the presentation but in general Iâ€™d avoid that (IM/chat can be useful for people to report issues with the presentation/audio).</li>\n<li>No attendee video<br>\nRecommended for large meetings (avoids network utilization).</li>\n<li>Hide names<br>\nNot necessarily needed (unless thereâ€™s special case).</li>\n<li>Everyone an attendee<br>\nMust have if not set in the invitation.</li>\n<li>Invite by email<br>\nRarely used (usually if you forgot to invite someone you can just add them to the conference manually)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"desktop-sharing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#desktop-sharing\" aria-label=\"desktop sharing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Desktop sharing</h3>\n<p>If any additional content (other than PowerPoint presentation) must be shared, itâ€™s generally preferred to use desktop sharing instead application sharing (it uses newer technology which is <a href=\"http://blog.schertz.name/2015/10/video-based-screen-sharing-in-skype-for-business/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Video Based Screen Sharing</a> and should work smoother). In addition, switching between windows is easier when you present your desktop than when you present specific application.</p>\n<p>  <strong>Note</strong>: if at least one of your participants joins using outdated client version, screensharing will anyway fallback to RDP (old technology) but usually there isn't much to avoid that.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2019-01-29 10:11","title":"Host Skype for Business meetings like a professional","description":"In that post I'd like to share some of the best practices for organizing meetings.","tags":["skype for business","outlook"]}}},"pageContext":{"id":"cf2c3b90-7e64-5f22-9a3f-5d56e37b86e1"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2483265550"]}